-- Hungary to Limit Monthly Telephone Tax to 700 Forint, Origo Says
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-05-02T16:28:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/hungary-to-limit-monthly-telephone-tax-to-700-forint-origo-says.html
Hungary plans to limit a proposed
monthly phone tax to 700 forint ($3.30) per person and to exempt
the first 10 minutes of each call, news website  Origo  reported,
citing Economy Minister  Gyorgy Matolcsy .  Most phone calls are shorter than 10 minutes, Matolcsy said
at a meeting of ruling party lawmakers today, according to
Origo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
